?cMS-Windows Installation|||

$BXTrkCad$ is shipped as a self-installing self-expanding program (executable).

Select the $BRun$ item from the $BStart menu$ (on MS-Windows).
Enter $BA:\XTC32310$ (replace 310 by the current version) if installing from the floppy.
Otherwise enter the complete path to $BXTrkCad$ installation program.

Alternatively, you can run $BXTC32310$ directly from MS-Windows Explorer.

The $BXTrkCad$ installation will prompt you for a directory name to
install $BXTrkCad$.  This directory will be the $BXTrkCad Install Directory$.

You will then be prompted to specify the Working Directory.  
You can choose:
?LSo
?LI
the Windows directory, which is directory used in older versions of $BXTrkCad$
?LI
the Install Directory
?LI
Custom Directory, and you will be prompted for the Directory name on the next dialog
?LE
If you have previously installed $BXTrkCad$ in another directory, you may want to copy the $Ixtrkcad.*$ files to the new directory.

The installation program will then proceed to install the files and build a Windows Program Group for $BXTrkCad$.

You can run $BXTrkCad$ by double clicking on the $BXTrkCad$ icon.

