?cQuick Tour|||

When $BXTrkCad$ starts, it displays the $XMain|mainW$ and $XMap|cmdMap$ windows.
The $BMap$ window is used to change the origin of the $BMain$ window when the entire layout
cannot be displayed at one time.

The Menu bar across the top of the $BMain$ window contains standard Windows menus.
Some of these are particularly useful to the new user:
?LSo
?LI
The $BFile|Open$ menu opens existing layout files.
When first installed, the default directory contains some example programs you can look at.
?LI
The $BFile|Exit$ menu exits $BXTrkCad$.  You can also exit by selecting the System menu in the upper left corner of the Window.
?LI
The $BOptions|Setup$ menu specifies the working scale and overall room size.
You will be limited to a roomsize of 96" x 48", unless 
you have $Xregistered|registration$ $BXTrkCad$
?LI
The $BOptions|Preferences$ menu specifies some less frequently changed items.
You can use this menu to choose $XMetric units|perfUnits$.
?LI
The $BHelp$ menu can be used to read the $BXTrkCad$ Help file (which you are reading now).
Also, the $BHelp|Demo$ menu selects a number of demonstrations which illustrate various features of $BXTrkCad$
