?cMouse Buttons|||

$BXTrkCad$ uses the left and right mouse buttons when manipulating tracks and
other objects on the layout.
Their meaning depends on the particular command but in general:
?LSo
?LI
$BLeft-Click$ - selects an object or an End-Point.
?LI
$BLeft-Drag$ - modifies an object, such as extending it.
?LI
$BRight-Click$ - displays a popup-menu of commands.
?LI
$BShift-Right-Click$ - displays a popup-menu of command options (for some commands).
?LE

?HdefRightClick
Note: the operation of $BRight-Click$ and $BShift-Right-Click$ can be flipped by $BRight Click$ item on the $XCommand Options|cmdCmdopt$ dialog.
This documentation will refer to $BShift-Right-Click$ as the default operation which displays a popup-menu of command options.

When Moving and Rotating ( Placing Turnouts and Structures,
Moving the Print and Snap Grids, ... ):
?LSo
?LI
$BLeft-Drag$ - moves the objects or grid.
?LI
$BRight-Drag$ - rotates the objects or grid about the pivot point, which is
the point you started the drag operation.
?LE

Some commands use the $BShift$ or $BControl$ key to modify the meaning of button presses.


?cDialogs|||

Most dialogs have three standard buttons:
?LSo
?LI
$BOk$ - Completes the dialog, and the layout is updated with the current changes.
?LI
$BCancel$ - Cancels the dialog, and the layout is reverted to its
previous state.
?LI
$BHelp$ - Invokes the on-line help for the current command or dialog.
?LE

Lengths and Distances can be entered in a variety of formats such as $B12ft 4 1/2in$, $B12' 4.5"$, $B148.500$, $B1.234m$, $B123.4cm$ or $B1234mm$.
Pressing the Equal Sign ($B=$) key after the entry will reformat the value in your $Xpreferred Length Format|lengthFormat$.
You can also press the $Bp$ key to convert a Prototype measurement to a Scale measurement by dividing by the ratio for the current scale.
The $Bs$ key will convert a Scale measurement to a Prototype measurement.


?cAccelerator Keys|||

Most commands have $Xaccelerator keys|commands$ defined which allow you to invoke the command
directly (instead of using the menus or the buttons on the $XTool Bar|toolbar$).

The $BReturn$ key has the same effect as pressing the $BOk$ button on the current dialog.

The $BEscape$ key cancels the current command.
All selected tracks are unselected.
The $XDescribe|cmdDescribe$ or $XSelect|cmdSelect$ command becomes the current command.

The $BPage Up$ and $BPage Down$ keys will zoom out or zoom in.

The arrows key will pan the canvas right, left, up and down. 

The $BDelete$ key invokes the $XDelete|cmdDelete$ command.

