?BPerformance Issues|performance||Performance
?Toverview

This section lists some things that can improve the performance of $BXTrkCad$.

?LSo
?LI
Use a hardware Floating Point Unit.
?LI
To speed up initialization, remove unused parameter files (see $XParameter Files|cmdPrmfile$ dialog).
?LI
During moves and rotates, draw tracks $BSimply$ or as $BEnd-Points$, (see the $XCommand Options|cmdCmdopt$ dialog).
Also $XZoom In|editZoomIn$ to reduce the number of tracks that are being displayed.
?LI
If you have to move a lot of track a large distance, create a temporary track at the destination and use the
$XJoin|cmdJoin$ command to move the selected track to join with the temporary track.  Then remove the temporary track.
?LI
Close the Map window if you don't need it to move about the layout.  The $XWindow|windowM$ menu can be used reopen the Map window.
?LI
On the $XDisplay|cmdDisplay$ dialog turn off drawing $BEnd-Points$, decrease the $BTwo Rail Scale$, increase $BMin Grid Spacing$, set $BDraw Ties$ to $BNone$ and turn off $BLive Map$.
?LI
Close any other unused applications.
