?cGENERAL XTRKCAD TERMS|||

$BEnd-Points$

One of the most important concepts in $BXTrkCad$ is the $BEnd-Point$.  
A piece of flex-track has an End-Point at each end.  
An End-Point has a position and an angle and it can be connected to other End-Points.  
The End-Points control where the track is placed 
and how it is connected.

Turnouts have several End-Points (normally 3).  
Turntables have a varying number.
?LS
?LI
?HactiveEndPoint
$BActive End-Point$ - when placing a turnout, the End-Point which is used as a 
'handle' when moved along other tracks.
?LI
?HselectedEndPoint
$BSelected End-Point$ - when selecting track for various reasons the 
$BSelected End-Point$ is the one closest to the selection point.
?LI
?HunconnectedEndPoint
$BUnconnected End-Point$ - an End-Point which is not connected to another.
?LE

$BOther Terms$
?LS
?LI
$BAuto-connect$ - when placing $Xturnouts|cmdHotBar$ and creating $Xparallel|cmdParallel$ tracks, the new track will automatically be connected to other tracks if the tracks are aligned properly.
?LI
$BEasements$ - a section of track with gradually changing radius which is used to smoothly 
connect tracks of differing radii.  Also known as Spiral Transition Curves.
?LI
$BError Message$ - an error message displayed in the $XStatus Bar|statusBar$ 
accompanied by a beep.
?LI
$BFlex-track$ - prefabricated track which may be formed into any suitable shape.  This term is also used for handlaid track.
?LI
$BInfo Message$ - an informational message displayed in the $XStatus Bar|statusBar$.
?LI
$BObject$ - an item on the layout, such as a track segment, table edge, line, note or text.
?LI
$BS-Curve$ - a curve which bends in one direction and then the other, forming an S-like shape.
?LI
$BSectional Track$ - prefabricated track which cannot be bent, split or changed.
?LI
$BTrack Segment$ - any piece of flex-track, turnout or sectional track.
?LI
$BTurnout$ - track which can switch the Train between two or more paths.  In $BXTrkCad$, $BTurnouts$ also include Sectional Tracks, crossings and forms of prefabricated (non-flex) track.
?LI
?HdefTurnoutFrog
$BTurnout Frog$ - the place on the Turnout track where one rail crosses the other.
?LI
?HdefTurnoutPoints
$BTurnout Points$ - the part of the Turnout that moves to select a path.
?LE

