?BBugs and Enhancements|bugs||Enhancements;Bugs
?Toverview
The file $Xxtrkcad.bug|directories$ contains the list of current bugs.

If you encounter a new bug please report it by sending a E-mail message to

    xtrkcad@sillub.com

Please indicate what you were doing, what you expected to happen and 
what did happen.  
If I need more detail I may ask you to make a recording.

If you can recreate the problem you can use $BMacro|Record$ 
to record what happened.  
Try to isolate the problem by creating a minimal layout and recording as 
few commands as possible.  

You may receive notice about an 'Audit' failure.  
This indicates an internal logic error in $BXTrkCad$ has been detected.  
An audit file can be generated which would be helpful in tracking 
down the problem.


I also welcome any suggestions for improvements to $BXTrkCad$.

Some of the areas under consideration are:
?LSo
?LI
More turnout definitions
?LI
Expanded demos
?LI
A tutorial manual
?LI
Dynamically change the cursor to reflect the operation
?LI
More track manipulation commands.
