?CLayers Dialog|cmdLayer||Commands;Layers
?Tdialogs

Each object is contained a Layer.
Objects which are created independently of other objects (such as $XStraight tracks|cmdStraight$ or $XText|cmdText$) are created in the current Layer.
Objects which are associated with other objects (such as tracks created by the $XModify|cmdModify$ or $XJoin|cmdJoin$ commands) are created in the same Layer as the associated object(s).

The $BLayers$ dialog allows you to change various attributes of each of the 99 $BLayers$.

Note: these attributes are stored with the current Layout.  They are not applied when you change Layouts.

?Gdlayer

The Drop List at the top of the dialog selects the $BLayer$ you are interested in.
Layers with some objects in the layer are preceeded by a $B+$.

The $BName$ Edit Box contains the name of the $BLayer$.  This name is listed in the $BCurrent Layer$ Drop List on the $XToolbar|toolbar$.  Also the $BName$ is displayed as the Balloon Help for the corresponding $BLayer Button$.

The $BColor$ Button specifies the color of tracks if $XLayer Colors|optionColorLayers$ Radio Button on the $BDisplay$ dialog is checked.

The $BVisible$ Toggle Button controls whether the $BLayer$ is drawn on the $XMain|mainW$ window.

The $BFrozen$ Toggle Button indicates that tracks in that $BLayer$ can not be modified or deleted.

The $BOn Map$ Toggle Button controls whether the $BLayer$ is drawn on the $XMap|cmdMap$ window.

You cannot uncheck $BVisible$ or check $BFrozen$ for the $BCurrent Layer$.

The $BCount$ field displays the number of objects in this Layer.

The bottom of the dialog contains the $BNumber of Layer Buttons$ Integer Edit Box. 
This controls the $BLayer Buttons$ displayed on the $XTool bar|toolbar$. 
Up to the first 20 $BLayer Buttons$ can be displayed.
You should use the first 20 layers for layers which you will be showing and hiding frequently.

?Gblayer

The $BLayer Buttons$ on the $XToolbar|toolbar$ control which Layer is the $Bcurrent Layer$ and which $BLayers$ are displayed on the Main Canvas.

The current Layer is selected by picking a value from the Drop Down Layer list.
If the Layer you've selected was not visible, it will be shown.

You can hide (or show if not visible) the different Layers by pushing one of the $BLayer Buttons$ on the toolbar (if you have configured the $Xtoolbar|toolbarM$ to show the Layer buttons).
If a Layer is not visible then the corresponding Layer button will be dimmed and
the underscore will be removed.
You cannot hide the current Layer.
These buttons are a short cut for the $BVisible$ Toggle button on the $BLayers$ dialog for the corresponding Layer.

The color of each layer button shows the color that will be used to draw 
tracks in that layer, if
you select $XColor Layers|optionColorLayers$ on the $BDisplay$ dialog.

Note: on some systems (with 256 color window drivers) all possible colors may not be displayed on the button faces.
In this case, Windows chooses the closest matching color which may be the same as the button background color.
In this case the number on the button will not be visible, however the correct color will be used to color objects in that layer.

Any selected objects are unselected when the Layer is made not visible.
If a Layer is not visible, you cannot select objects in the Layer.
It is as if the objects do not exist until you show the Layer again.

The $BMove To Current Layer$ command on $XTools menu|toolsM$ will move all $Xselected|cmdSelect$ tracks to the current Layer.

Objects are drawn on the map window, if the Layer they are on has $BOn Map$ checked.


