?BDescribe Command|cmdDescribe|bdescrib|Commands;Describe
?Tcommands
The $BDescribe$ button will cancel any other command in progress.  
Any auxiliary dialogs are closed and the main window is restored.

Clicking on any object while in $BDescribe$ mode will display the Property Sheet for the object listing such things as its position, size, color and layer as appropriate for each type of object.
Certain values can be changed to modify the object.
If a track is connected to other tracks, then some values (ie. End Point positions) can not be changed.

The object is highlighted by a grey area.

Most commands return to $BDescribe$ mode then they terminate unless the command is $Xsticky|cmdSticky$.

Note: the Default Command radio button on the $XCommand Options|cmdCmdopt$ dialog controls whether the $BDescribe$ or
the $XSelect|cmdSelect$ command is used as the default command.

?BSelect Command|cmdSelect|bselect|Commands;Select
?Tcommands
The $BSelect$ button will cancel any other command in progress.
Any auxiliary windows are closed and the main window is restored.

?LSo
?LI
$BLeft-Click$ - selects an object (or unselects a selected object).
?LI
$BShift-Left-Click$ - selects all unselected tracks connected to the track you select.
Selection stops at selected tracks.
Caution: This can select all tracks on the layout.
?LI
$BLeft-Drag$ - highlights an area, and all objects within the area are selected.
?LI
$BRight-Click$ - displays a popup-menu of commands.
?LI
$XShift-Right-Click|defRightClick$ - displays a popup-menu of options controlling how objects are drawn during moves and rotates (see below).  If there are selected objects then additional menu items allow you to rotate the selected objects by various angles.
?LI
$BRight-Drag$ - highlights an area, and all objects within the area are unselected.
?LI
$BShift-Left-Drag$ - moves the selected objects (see the $XMove|cmdMove$ command).
?LI
$BShift-Right-Drag$ - rotates the selected objects (see the $XRotate|cmdRotate$ command).
If you press the $BControl$ key while Dragging then rotation will be done in increments of 15.
?LI
$BControl-Left-Drag$ - moves Turnout and Elevations labels (see the $XMove Label|cmdMoveLabel$ command).
?LE

Also the $BSelect All$ menu item on the $XEdit|editM$ menu selects all objects on the layout.

$BSelected$ objects are drawn in $BRed$ (unless changed in the $XColor|cmdRgbcolor$ dialog).

Note: To select a $XFilled Shape|cmdDraw$, click on its edge.

Connections between selected and unselected tracks will be broken when 
selected tracks are moved.  
If the Drawing Scale is 8:1 or smaller, these about-to-be broken connections are marked with 
a red X.

The $BDraw Moving Tracks$ Radio box on the $XCommand Options|cmdCmdopt$ dialog selects how objects are drawn during drags to move or rotate objects.
This can be time-consuming when using a large number of objects.
The options are:
?LSo
?LI
$BNormal$ - objects are drawn normally.
?LI
$BSimple$ - objects are drawn using one line (instead of two when zoomed in), structures are drawn as outlines, no End-Points or lines are drawn
?LI
$BEnd Points$ - only the End-Points are drawn (as stars).
?LE

The following commands operate on the objects you have selected:
?LSo
?LI
$XMove|cmdMove$ the selected objects.
?LI
$XRotate|cmdRotate$ the selected objects.
?LI
$XFlip|cmdFlip$ (mirrors) the selected objects.
?LI
$XDelete|cmdDelete$ selected objects.
?LI
Hide (or unhide) in a $XTunnel|cmdTunnel$.
?LI
Move $XAbove or Below|cmdAboveBelow$.
?LI
$XParts List|cmdEnum$ of the selected objects.
?LI
Change the width of the tracks' rails.
?LI
$XExport|cmdExport$ the selected objects.
?LI
Creates a Structure or Turnout definition from $XGrouped|cmdGroup$ objects.
?LI
$XRescale|cmdRescale$ the selected objects.
?LE

In addition the $BCut$, $BCopy$ and $BPaste$ commands on the $XEdit|editM$ menu operate on the selected objects.

Note: the Default Command radio button on the $XCommand Options|cmdCmdopt$ dialog controls whether the $XDescribe|cmdDescribe$ or
the $BSelect$ command is used as the default command.

Pressing the $BEscape$ key will deselect all selected tracks.

