?Gtrainbar

$BSelecting New Cars$

The Hot Bar contains the Cars and Locomotives which are have not been placed on the Layout.
Cars are created and managed using the $XCar Inventory|cmdCarinv$ dialog.

Each item on the Hot Bar can represent a group of Cars.
Cars can be grouped by Prototype, Manufacturer and/or Part Number.
They can also be listed as individual Car Items.
This grouping is controlled by $BCar Labels$ Drop Down List on the $XDisplay|cmdDisplay$ dialog.

To place a Car, select it from the Hot Bar.
If the Hot Bar is displaying Cars in groups (and not as individual Car Items) then a Drop Down List is displayed on the $XStatus Bar|statusBar$ containing the individual Car Items in that group.

$Gbnewcar$ If you are not displaying the Hot Bar, then the $BNew Car$ button will be shown on the Tool Bar.
Pressing this button will display the Drop Down List on the $XStatus Bar|statusBar$ containing all of your Car Items that have not yet been placed on the layout.

$BPlacing Cars$

Once you have selected a new Car, or have selected an existing Car on the Layout, you can position it by dragging it on the Layout.
If the Car is coupled to other Cars then the whole set of Cars is moved.
If you place the Car on a Track, then Car (and the other coupled Cars) will be aligned along the track.

Note: if you move the tracks but not the cars (or vice-versa) using the $XMove|cmdMove$ or $XRotate|cmdRotate$ commands the cars will not remain attached to the tracks.  If the cars are moved close to a track, then they will be aligned when the $BTrain Simulation$ command is next invoked.

$BCoupling Cars$

If you move a Car along a track to another Car then the Cars will be coupled together.
To uncouple Cars, Right-Click between the Cars and select Uncouple from the pop-up menu.

$BTrains$

A Train consists of one or more Locomotives coupled to other Cars.
One Locomotive will be the $BMU Master$ for the Train.
The $BMU Master$ can be changed by Right-Clicking on a Locomotive and selecting $BMU Master$ from the pop-up menu.
The $BMU Master$ is drawn with a solid Yellow head light indicating the direction is moving.
If a Train is split by uncoupling between Locomotives, then two Trains will be created, each with their own $BMU Master$

