$BTrain Control$

?Gtrain

The $BTrain Control$ dialog is used to set the speed and direction of Trains.
The dialog contains a list of Trains (listed by their $BMU Master$ Locomotive).
Before each Train on the list is either a Red circle (indicating the Train is stopped) or a Green circle (indicating the Train is moving).

Any number of Trains can be running, although it might be difficult to keep track of more than a few.

For the selected Train, the Train Control dialog lists
?LSo
?LI
Train status: indicating that the Train is moving, is paused or the reason if the Train is stopped.
?LI
The position of the Train
?LI
A slider which controls the speed of the Train in Scale Miles-Per-Hour or Kilometers-Per-Hour.
?LI
The Odometer which measures the total distance travelled by the train, which can be reset by pressing the $B0$ button.
?LI
The $BFind$ button which positions the $XMain Window|mainW$ to show the Train.
If the Train on a track that is hidden and $XTrains on Hidden Track|cmdDisplay$ is set to $BHide$, then the Train will be made visible until the next time it moves.
?LI
The $BFollow$ toggle button which causes the $XMain Window|mainW$ to follow the Train as it moves.
The $BFollow$ toggle can only be set on one Train at a time, and it is cleared if you press the $BFind$ button or otherwise manually move the main canvas.
?LI
The $BAuto Reverse$ toggle button which causes the Train to change direction when it hits the end of a track.
?LI
The Direction radio button group which controls the direction ($BForward$ or $BReverse$) of the Train.
?LI
The $BStop$ button which sets the Train's speed to 0.
?LE


$BTrain Operation$

Once a Train is moving, it will continue to move until it is Stopped manually, hits the end of track or an open Turnout.
If the Train 'runs into' other Cars, those Cars will be coupled to the Train.
If Train's speed is faster than the $XMax Coupling Speed|maxcouplingspeed$ then the Train will crash and must be manually moved back onto the track.

If two Trains are coupled, one of the two $BMU Masters$ will be chosen as the $BMU Master$ for the combined Train.

The motion of all Trains can be Paused by clicking the $BGo/Stop$ button on the Main Window Tool Bar.
Pressing the $BEscape$ key has the same effect as clicking on the $BStop$ button.
This allows you set Turnout positions or make other changes.
When Train command starts, the $BGo/Stop$ button is in the $BStop$ position and must be clicked before Trains move.

$BTurnouts and Turntables$

Turnout positions are indicated by Red lines connecting the End-Points on the route through the Turnout.
Trains will follow this route through the Turnout.
If you Shift-Left-Click on the Turnout, the next position will used and Red line changed to indicate the new position.

Turntables can be turned by Shift-Left-Clicking on the End-Point you want the Turntable to move to.
To turn the Turntable 180, Shift-Left-Click on the End-Point again.


