The $BDraw$ commands are used to draw lines, arcs and other shapes. 
These can be used to represent water edges, bridges and other scenic features.

There are 4 command buttons on the toolbar used to draw Straight Objects, Curved Lines, Circles and other Shapes.
Each command button is followed by a button that changes the action (and Icon) on the command button.

Some commands display controls on the $XStatus Line|statusBar$ to change line width, color or other attributes of the object.

?LSo
?LI
Straight Objects are created by $XLeft-Dragging|leftdrag$ on the layout.
If $BDraw Straight Objects$ is $XSticky|cmdSticky$, $BShift-Left-Drag$ will use the End-Point of the previous line as the starting point.
?LS
?LI
$Gdline$ Creates a $BStraight Line$ of specified color and width.
?LI
$Gddimlin$ Creates a $BDimension Line$ of various sizes.
?LI
$Gdbench$ Creates $BBenchwork$ using different types and orientation of lumber.
?LI
$Gdtbledge$ Creates a $BTable Edge$
?LE

?LI
$BCurved Lines$ are created in the same manner as curved tracks.
?LS
?LI
$Gdcurve1$ Select the start of the curve and drag in the direction of the curve.
?LI
$Gdcurve2$ Select one end of the curve and drag to the center.
?LI
$Gdcurve3$ Select the center of the curve and drag to one end.
?LI
$Gdcurve4$ Drag from one end of the curve to the other to form the chord of the curve.
?LE
Next drag on the Red arrows to adjust the curve.

?LI
$BCircles$ and $BFilled Circles$ are created by selecting either the center position or a point on the edge of the circle and dragging to specify the radius.
?LS
?LI
$Gdcircle2$ $Gdflcrcl2$ Select a point on the edge of the circle and drag to the center.
?LI
$Gdcircle3$ $Gdflcrcl3$ Select the center and drag to set the radius.
